It's really admirable how John Meadows brought his gym buddy to almost every single video he made, had him show the exercises together with him, filmed him lifting, etc. Just trying to share as much of the fame and spotlight with his friend as possible. Very noble. Mountain Dog.

Used to rummage through my high school's locked basement storage room full of old computers and drawers with keyboards, mouses, etc. and check local computer repair stores with second hand hardware hoping to find something like this or an IBM Model M keyboard back in the day.

Never was big into the world of technology or computers myself, but there is still something very alluring about ancient and forgotten devices/hardware. Space-cadet keyboards, punching card tabulating machines, trackballs, older Linux distros. I did find a very vintage IBM mouse.

I got into Linux (and am still a fan) because I enjoy the ability to customize stuff, but to really understand computers you need to be good at math and coding didn't appeal to me... I can see myself trying to design ergonomic keyboards or something one day...
